headline: FactSet (FDS): Profit Margins Climb, Supporting Narrative of Undervalued Stability
summary: FactSet Research Systems (FDS) posted a solid year with earnings rising 11.2%, well ahead of its 5-year average growth of 9.1% per year. Net profit margins also improved to 25.7%, up from 24.4% last year, even as earnings and revenue forecasts for the coming years trail the broader US market. Investors are sizing up the notably low Price-To-Earnings ratio of 18x, which positions the stock as a potential value play compared to industry and peer averages.
